The paper deals with distributed computing and fault tolerance, which are typical topics in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the presence of an adversary and the use of cryptography, which are relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The algorithm presented in the paper involves communication and information theory, which are relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of private channels and flooding, which are relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of Byzantine agreement, which is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
